title: For Sale:  Well G96 Sniper Rifle Airsoft AICS G96-D with Scope & Bipod Excellent Condition
postcontent:
This is a Well G96 airsoft rifle.

I bought this last week with the plans on modding the stock for a Savage rimfire rifle, but once I rec'd it, I realize it really isn't my cup of tea (google "well g96 savage" to see what I'm talking about).

I'm not an airsoft guy, so I really can't comment much on the gun itself. Two issues I was told about when I bought the gun is that the bolt catch is broken/missing (see pic), and the magazine leaks. Both seem to be fairly common issues with this gun, and easily fixable (in fact I found a youtube video on repairing the magazine by replacing o-rings). But then again, you only need the stock if you're doing the build like I had planned, and that is in great shape.

Comes with scope, mount, bipod, ect. What you see is what you get.

This is the original description the individual I bought it from gave:

"Features:

    * Gas Powered
    * Full Metal Construction
    * Durable Plastic Receiver
    * Adjustable Hop Up
    * Gas Bolt Action
    * 20Round cap Magazine
    * 3-9x40mm Sniper scope with specialized L96 type ring mount
    * Full metal bipod and bipod tri rail adapter quick detachable
    * Foldable Stock for easy storage
    * Adjustable Rubberized butt stock and cheek rest
    * Adjustable Retactable Monopod
    * AWS Full Metal Flash Hider

Includes:

    * Gas G96
    * 20r G96 Magazine
    * Full Metal Bipod
    * 3-9x40mm Sniper Scope

FPS:
    *515fps


This is a gas G96 L96 Sniper rifle, it is very heavy compare to the spring version, the magazine is very durable and holds a lot of gas for 4 reloads or more depending on temperature. The upper barrel assembly is made from solid metal, adds extra weight to the rifle. The stock has every feature a sniper desires. Sling mounts are located at the front of the hand guard and at the stock. The magazine placement is at the right location, a very well made replica of the Ares G96. There are a a few loose paint located at the handguard and at the grip, I have field this 3 times and has gotten many heads with .40 bbs, but I was using a 50mm scope, this included scope would require zeroing in.

The sniper rifle is currently missing the bolt catch to function, a small part located near the bolt and can be replaced easily. The magazine also has leaking issues. All sales are final, selling this item as is."

Happy to ship on buyer's dime, 18lb from 14623.

title: For Sale:  A weekend of shooting fun!
postcontent: Read this if you enjoy shooting guns!! Only one week left to register for this amazing event guys and gals!  Are you bored with the typical range session? Standing still and shooting paper no longer interest you? We have the solution! A couple buddies and I sat down one day and decided to change the way we shoot. We all had the tacticool rifles and pistols. We had a pile of ammo suitable for a Zombie invasion. We had vests, holsters, and other gear. But we never put all this stuff to use the way it was intended. We started up a club and named it RAC FRAG, or Responsible Armed Citizens, Fun Run And Gun. We made custom steel targets. We made shooting stations. We set up a course that involves running from station to station and shooting the steel targets at various ranges. We transition from long range rifle targets to close range pistol targets, and back again. You can't help but smile when you hear that BANG on the steel plates. Every gunner gets videoed and timed on their run so it puts a touch of stress into the mix. This course teaches you how to set up your gear, make quick mag changes, shoot while on the move, and shoot while shaking and out of breath. We found a fantastic piece of land near Madison Lake MN that we leased to hold our events. Here is a link to my worst run of the day during our last event to show you we are not super tactical operators and you have nothing to be intimidated by: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dG9hslsjdRw We are all having an absolutely fantastic time doing this. If you don't have guns and you want to run with us, we have plenty of guns for you to borrow at no cost as long as you pay for the ammo.  Even if you have never shot a gun before and have always wanted to, this is a great place to get started!  Our next big shoot is this coming weekend, Saturday, June 28, and we are also going to camp out and shoot all day Sunday too for anybody that might want to join us. Cost is $75 per person, or $120 to camp overnight and have another day of shooting fun. We have a generator on site, a portable toilet, and a grill for whatever you want to bring to cook.  We are looking for more people to add to our club so if this sounds like something you might be interested in, respond to this ad or call/text me and lets chat! REDACTED Please let me know if you have any questions or if you want more info. Check out our website for more pics and videos: http://rac-frag.weebly.com/ Feel free to register on our home page for our June 28 shoot to hold your spot. If you register, you will also be placed on our mailing list for regular FRAG updates. Thanks!! Cody

title: Want To Buy:  Hi Point C9
postcontent:
Looking to buy a Hi Point C9.

Yes, I'm 18

http://myfreedomfoundation.com/blog/liberty-live/detail/can-individuals-between-18-and-20-purchase-and-own-handguns> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-132
Possession of a handgun by a person under the age of 18 years

Georgia law only covers possession of handguns by those 
"Under" the age of 18 with varying circumstances, as well as those 21+. That means a person 18-20 can legally "posses" a handgun.


O.C.G.A. § 16-11-101.1
Furnishing pistol or revolver to person under the age of 18 years

This law relates to the sale of handguns in Georgia through a private party (you and I) sale. Once again, it only refers to those "under" the age of 18. The rest of the laws that apply to the sale of handguns and handgun ammunition in Georgia are federal laws which only apply to an FFL or manufacturer. (http://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/articles/2004/citizen%60s-guide-to-federal-firearms-law.aspx> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-126
Having or carrying handguns, long guns, or other weapons; license requirement; exceptions for homes, motor vehicles, and other locations and conditions; penalties for violations

A person of age 18-20 is treated as an adult who does not have a Georgia Weapons Carry License, and must abide by those same rules. Those rules, in short, mean that the handgun may not leave the confines of my home (property of said home included), motor vehicle, and/or place of business

It has a 1000-yard BDC and a 3000-yard range finder built-in. The custom designed mounting ring of ATN riflescopes, which incorporates the BDC, insures easy and precise adjustments. The 80mm lens is one of the largest objective lenses available giving you the brightest image possible. ATN Rifle scope Professional 12-36x80 has an electronic reticle. There is 10 degrees of illumination. The rheostat is the knob located at the back of the scope. It is labeled with numbers 0 through 10. When the rheostat is set at 0 you will see a black etched reticle. The reticle will light up red electronically as you rotate the rheostat through the numbers, 10 being the brightest. The rangefinder reticle in ATN Riflescope Professional was designed to assist you in determining the range of your target. These distances are based on a 6' target, if a 6' target fits between the numbered baseline (the seven short horizontal lines) and the post of the reticle above the baseline determines your distance. If a 6' target fits between the horizontal post of the reticle and 2 the target is 200 yards away. If the same target fits between the 4 and the horizontal post of the reticle the target is 400 yards away. The same is with the 6, 8, 10, 20 and 30.
